## Brain vs hands - decouple reasoning from execution
direction: down

intro: {
  shape: text
  label: "Production agents use TWO models, not one:\n- BRAIN: expensive reasoning model (plans, decides, reflects)\n- HANDS: cheap/fast model (executes tool calls, parses, formats)\nDifferent strengths, different cost profiles, different SLAs."
  style.italic: true
  style.font-color: "#7c3aed"
}

oneModel: {
  label: "ONE MODEL (naive)"
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#fee2e2"
  style.stroke: "#dc2626"
  body: {label: "Single LLM does everything:\n- High-level planning\n- Code generation\n- Tool call formatting\n- Response synthesis\n\nProblem: pay reasoning-model prices for\nstring formatting; pay reasoning latency\nfor parse tasks; one bottleneck for all."; shape: text}
}

twoModel: {
  label: "BRAIN + HANDS (decoupled)"
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#bbf7d0"
  style.stroke: "#16a34a"
  body: {label: "BRAIN (Claude Opus / o3 / Gemini Ultra):\n- Plans the task\n- Decides next action\n- Reflects on results\n- Long-horizon reasoning\n\nHANDS (Haiku / Flash / Mini):\n- Formats tool calls\n- Extracts structured data\n- Summarizes results\n- Routes / classifies\n\nResult: 5-10x cost reduction, lower latency\non hot path, better quality everywhere."; shape: text}
}

orchestration: {
  label: "Orchestration"
  shape: rectangle
  style.fill: "#fde68a"
  style.stroke: "#d97706"
  body: {label: "Brain produces a plan ('do X, then Y').\nHarness routes each step to brain or hands.\nHands handles deterministic / formatting steps.\nBrain handles reasoning / decision steps.\n\nCommon split:\n  ~20% of calls = brain\n  ~80% of calls = hands\n  ~80% of cost  = brain"; shape: text}
}

intro -> oneModel
intro -> twoModel
oneModel -> orchestration: "vs"
twoModel -> orchestration
